{"title_page": "1967\u201368 Yugoslav First League", "text_new": "{{Infobox football league season\n| competition        = [[Yugoslav First League|Prva savezna liga]]\n| season             = 1967&ndash;68\n| dates = {{Nowrap|20 August 1967 \u2013 30 June 1968}}\n| winners            = [[Red Star Belgrade|Red Star]] (8th title)\n| relegated          = None\n| continentalcup1    = [[1968\u201369 European Cup|European Cup]]\n| continentalcup1 qualifiers =  [[Red Star Belgrade|Red Star]]\n| continentalcup2    = [[1968\u201369 European Cup Winners' Cup|Cup Winners' Cup]]\n| continentalcup2 qualifiers =  [[FK Bor|Bor]]\n| continentalcup3    = [[1968\u201369 Inter-Cities Fairs Cup|Inter-Cities Fairs Cup]]\n| continentalcup3 qualifiers =  [[NK Dinamo Zagreb|Dinamo Zagreb]]<br>[[NK Olimpija Ljubljana (1911)|Olimpija]]<br>[[FK Vojvodina|Vojvodina]]<br />[[OFK Belgrade]]\n| league topscorer   = [[Slobodan Santra\u010d]] (22)\n| biggest home win   = \n| biggest away win   = \n| highest scoring    = \n| matches            = \n| total goals        = \n| longest wins       = \n| longest unbeaten   = \n| longest losses     = \n| highest attendance = \n| lowest attendance  = \n| average attendance = \n| prevseason         = [[1966\u201367 Yugoslav First League|1966\u201367]]\n| nextseason         = [[1968\u201369 Yugoslav First League|1968\u201369]]\n}}\n\nThe '''1967\u201368 [[Yugoslav First League]] season''' was the 22nd season of the First Federal League ({{lang-sh|Prva savezna liga}}), the top level [[association football]] league of [[SFR Yugoslavia]], since its establishment in 1946. Sixteen teams contested the competition, with [[Red Star Belgrade|Red Star]] winning their eighth national title.\n\n==Teams==\nAt the end of the previous season [[FK Sutjeska Nik\u0161i\u0107|Sutjeska]] and [[NK \u010celik Zenica|\u010celik]] were relegated. They were replaced by [[FK Proleter Zrenjanin|Proleter Zrenjanin]] and [[NK Maribor|Maribor]].\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"t