son || [[Robert Aldrich]] || [[Seven Arts Productions|Seven Arts]]\n|-\n| 1963 || ''[[The Caretakers]]'' || Lucretia Terry || [[Hall Bartlett]] || [[United Artists]]\n|-\n| 1964 || ''[[Strait-Jacket]]'' || Lucy Harbin || [[William Castle]] || [[Columbia Pictures|Columbia]]\n|-\n| 1964 || ''[[Della (film)|Della]]''<ref>TV movie pilot for ''Royal Bay'' unsold series, released theatrically</ref> || Della Chappell || [[Robert Gist]] || [[Four Star Television|Four Star]]\n|-\n| 1965 || ''[[I Saw What You Did]]'' || Amy Nelson || [[William Castle]] || [[Universal Pictures|Universal]]\n|-\n| 1967 || ''[[The Karate Killers]]''<ref>Feature film culled from 2-part episode of ''The Man from U.N.C.L.E.''</ref> || Amanda True || [[Barry Shear]] || [[Metro-Goldwyn-Mayer]]\n|-\n| 1967 || ''[[Berserk!]]'' || Monica Rivers || [[Jim O'Connolly]] || [[Columbia Pictures|Columbia]]\n|-\n| 1970 || ''[[Trog]]'' || Dr. Brockton || [[Freddie Francis]] || [[Warner Bros.]]\n|}\n\n\u2021 denotes lost film\n\n====Short subjects====\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders sortable\"\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! Director\n! Studio\n|-\n| 1925 || ''MGM Studio Tour'' || Herself<ref name=\"lucille\" /> || \u2013 || [[Metro-Goldwyn-Mayer]]\n|-\n| 1925 || ''Miss MGM'' || Miss MGM<ref name=\"uncredited\" /> || \u2013 || [[Metro-Goldwyn-Mayer]]\n|-\n| 1930 || ''Hollywood Snapshots #11'' || Herself || [[Ralph Staub]] || [[Columbia Pictures|Columbia]]\n|-\n| 1931 || ''[[The Stolen Jools|The Slippery Pearls]]'' || Herself || [[William C. McGann]] || [[Paramount Pictures|Paramount]]\n|-\n| 1932 || ''[[Screen Snapshots]]'' || Herself || [[Ralph Staub]] || [[Columbia Pictures|Columbia]]\n|-\n| 1947 || ''[[The Jimmy Fund]]'' || Herself || \u2013 || \u2013\n|-\n| 1958 || ''Hollywood Mothers and Fathers'' || Herself || \u2013 ||[[Columbia Pictures|Columbia]]\n|-\n| 1972 || ''A Very Special Child'' || Narrator || \u2013 || [[American Cancer Society]]\n|}\n\n====Archival footage====\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowhead